<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Re: Neat. I have another idea completely opposite.</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Benign">Benign</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 8:07 p.m. 22/6/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: Neat. I have another idea completely opposite.<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=2216" TARGET=_self>Re: Neat. I have another idea completely opposite.</A> (Eirik the Red, UDL)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>I say death is for PvP or NPC. Forcing people to group and be safe. You wouldnt see small goups of people jumping into the 50's(level) because the risk for getting really good XP would weigh too heavy against the risk of dying. I believe people would make the higher levels pretty quickly anyways(guilds will be guilds). Running would just be more of an option. The resurrection spell would finally be worth a damn(more of a damn for those of you that REALLY like it). It would force some serious mass grouping issues into effect. You could actually fight and defeat an enemy guild or just enemy for that matter. I think it would be a terrific experiment for the future of gaming.

</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
